<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-11399] STC: inferred type of closure delegate, owner and thisObject</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-11399</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The inferred type of &quot;delegate&quot;, &quot;owner&quot;, &quot;thisObject&quot;, &quot;getDelegate()&quot;, &quot;getOwner()&quot; and &quot;getThisObject()&quot; within a closure has a few problems.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) All should infer to &lt;tt&gt;Class&amp;lt;Type&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt; when in a static context (and no nesting or delegation metadata is present).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) &lt;tt&gt;getOwner()&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;getThisObject()&lt;/tt&gt; infer to the enclosing type regardless of the object expression when inside a closure.  And the same for &lt;tt&gt;getDelegate()&lt;/tt&gt; if no delegation metadata is found.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3) &lt;tt&gt;getOwner()&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;getDelegate&lt;/tt&gt; (if no delegation metadata is found) should infer to &lt;tt&gt;Closure&lt;/tt&gt; within a nested closure block.  &lt;tt&gt;StaticTypeCheckingVisitor#visitVariableExpression&lt;/tt&gt; does this for &quot;owner&quot; and &quot;delegate&quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-5470&quot; title=&quot;@TypeChecked Closure methods/properties not recognized inside closure defition&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-5470&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-5470&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-6091&quot; title=&quot;Explicit use of &amp;quot;delegate&amp;quot; doesn&amp;#39;t make use of @DelegatesTo&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-6091&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-6091&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-9604&quot; title=&quot;STC: method or property missing errors for Closure&amp;#39;s getResolveStrategy(), etc.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-9604&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-9604&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
